Make a graph

  1. Tell R were using ggplot
  2. Tell R what data were using, and what variables we want to plot
  3. What type of graph were creating (geom)
ggplot(data = THIS, aes(x = THIS, y = THIS)) +
  geom_THIS()

Now lets create a graph of CI visitation:

ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors)) +
  geom_line()

ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors)) +
  geom_point()

  1. Create a column graph with this data
  2. Create an area graph with this data
ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors)) +
  geom_area()

Intro to customizing ggplot graphs

  • color = (update point or line color)
  • fill = (update the fill characteristic of an element)
  • linetype =
  • pch = (value)
  • size =
  • alpha =
ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors)) +
  geom_line(color = "green",
            linetype = "dashed")

ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors)) +
  geom_point(color = "blue",
             pch = 17,
             size = 4,
             alpha = 0.5)
